  "name": "Intuitive Protection",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/spells/enchant-red-3.jpg",
  "sort": 0,
  "flags": {},
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When a conjuration (summoning) spell is cast by an opponent and the magus successfully identifies the spell with a Spellcraft check, he can spend 1 point form his arcane pool as an immediate action to cast protection from chaos, evil, good, or law (chosen when using this ability) on himself; this lasts a number of rounds equal to his magus level. At 7th level, he can instead cast magic circle against chaos, evil, good, or law when using this ability.</p>\n<p>The magus must be at least 3rd level before selecting this arcana.</p>"
    },
